  "text": "A ring R with A r (R) = J(R) need not be in any of the classes in Example 26. We have A r (Z) = J(Z) = Z f1; 1g but Z is not semipotent; the localization Z [CITATION_1] of the integers at 2 is a domain that satis…es A r = J (it is local and so semipotent) but, as is readily veri…ed, it is not right Kasch, not left principally injective, and not left C2.",
